      • updateKeyWords

        void updateKeyWords(int selectedTab)
        Helper function called before LogParse. Fills the keyWords set with the set of keywords that the parser uses to base its searches off of. Function is only called when the user is selecting from the CheckBoxTree or from the group view
        Parameters:
        selectedTab - The current tab in the treeview

      • createTreeView

        void createTreeView()
        Helper function that generates the CheckBoxTree view and adds a mouselistener to the tree to aid selection. At the end of the function, it calls updateTreeView() which fills the DefaultTreeModel with nodes from the treeMap HashMap.

      • updateTreeView

        protected void updateTreeView()
        Used as a helper function for the createTreeView() function and also updates the checkbox tree dynamically as the administrator makes changes to the database.
